{
  "unmapped_findings": [
    "The 15Mn5Ni alloy exhibited brittle behavior with tensile elongation <1% when heat treated at 973 K and 1023 K, and stress-strain curves could not be recorded for these conditions.",
    "The B2 phase in 15Mn5Ni alloy underwent shearing and fragmentation at 35-45 degrees to rolling direction during cold rolling.",
    "The dissolution rate of finer intragranular B2 particles was higher than that of B2 stringers.",
    "The strain hardening exponent n varied from 0.16 to 0.50 depending on alloy composition and heat treatment temperature.",
    "Fractography revealed dimple morphology for 28Mn0Ni and 28Mn5Ni (ductile failure) but quasi-cleavage fracture with intergranular cracking for 15Mn5Ni at 1023 K.",
    "Planar slip activity followed by dynamic slip band refinement was observed as the dominant deformation mechanism in fully recrystallized austenite.",
    "The Mn/Ni ratio played a vital role in controlling precipitation, recrystallization kinetics, and mechanical properties."
  ],
